## requireAuth() Implementation

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[API Route Called] --> B[await requireAuth<br/>allowedRoles?]

    B --> C[Get auth from Clerk]
    C --> D{User authenticated?}

    D -->|No| E[Return 401 Unauthorized<br/>error: Not authenticated]

    D -->|Yes| F[Query users table<br/>WHERE clerkUserId = ?]

    F --> G{User exists in DB?}
    G -->|No| H[Return 404 Not Found<br/>error: User not found]

    G -->|Yes| I{Role check needed?}
    I -->|No| J[Return { user, userId }]
    I -->|Yes| K{Has allowed role?}

    K -->|No| L[Return 403 Forbidden<br/>error: Insufficient permissions]
    K -->|Yes| J

    style E fill:#f8d7da
    style H fill:#f8d7da
    style L fill:#f8d7da
    style J fill:#d4edda
```

**Code Location:** `src/lib/auth-utils.ts`

```typescript
export async function requireAuth(allowedRoles?: UserRole[]) {
  const { userId: clerkUserId } = await auth();
  if (!clerkUserId) {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Not authenticated' }, { status: 401 });
  }

  const user = await db.select().from(users)
    .where(eq(users.clerkUserId, clerkUserId))
    .limit(1);

  if (user.length === 0) {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'User not found' }, { status: 404 });
  }

  if (allowedRoles && !allowedRoles.includes(user[0].type as UserRole)) {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Insufficient permissions' }, { status: 403 });
  }

  return { user: user[0], userId: user[0].id };
}
```

